text: Zeulenroda-Triebes is a German town in the rural district of Greiz in Thuringia. It has about 18,000 inhabitants. Most famous sight of the town is the beautiful town hall. == Other websites == * Official website of Zeulenroda-Triebes * Landkreis Greiz Category:Verwaltungsgemeinschaftfrei towns in Thuringia Category:Greiz Rural District
